reviewerName: John S. Harris "The Voice of Reason"
reviewText: From the looks of it, this is a foreign label re-issue of the "Two Against Nature" concert DVD from several years back.  No new footage, no new music, no reason to purchase it.  If you want this DVD I'd suggest you buy the original release instead.5-star concert but 3-star DVD release for it being a re-issue and a head fake.
summary: Foreign label re-issue of existing DVD
Title: N/A

reviewText: I have never seen Steely Dan perform before.  I was always curious about who plays what and who sings what.  The liner notes on the CDs give inaccurate and contradictory information.  The audio and video quality of my "Steely Dan: In Concert" DVD is excellent and it is widescreen!  Perhaps some bogus or unlicensed DVDs were released previously, but the pedigree of this DVD (it is an import from the Netherlands) seems legitimate to me!  Thanks for the heads-up that this is identical to the "Two Against Nature" DVD (although Amazon describes the "TAN" DVD being almost 30 minutes longer the the "In Concert" DVD)..  I will avoid purchasing that rare and costly DVD.  I am delighted with my DVD.  I am sorry to hear that some of you got ripped-off with an inferior product.  My copy from Red Tag Market in Amazon Marketplace gets 5 stars from me
